**Appendix D -- Holiday Pay**

On your current schedule, there are 8 regular holidays plus 2 bonus
holidays. On your current schedule, you work an 8-hour shift and get 8
hours of holiday pay every holiday. The calculations below assume that
you take the holiday off, miss 8 hours and get 8 hours of holiday pay to
make up for the lost hours.

![](media/image19.emf)

On the 12-hour schedules, there are still 8 regular holidays plus 2
bonus holidays. On 12-hour schedules, you only work 50% of the days in
the year. This means that, on average, a regular holiday will fall on
half of the days you are scheduled to work and on half of the days you
are scheduled off. A bonus holiday will always fall on a workday. If a
holiday falls on a workday, you miss 12 hours of work and get 12 hours
of pay on that day. If a holiday falls on a day off, you get 8 hours of
holiday pay even though you missed no work. In the end, you can see that
you do not lose money due to this way of paying holiday pay. In fact,
you gain 32 hours of holiday pay per year, on average.

